# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 15 design system project with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.

## Key Files and Directories

- **Main entry point**: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - The main page showcasing all components
- **Component exports**: [src/components/index.ts](mdc:src/components/index.ts) - Centralized component exports
- **Global styles**: [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - CSS variables and global styles
- **Tailwind config**: [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Custom theme and design tokens
- **TypeScript config**: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path mapping

## Component Organization

All components are located in `src/components/` and follow these patterns:
- Each component has its own file (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `Typography.tsx`)
- Components are exported from [src/components/index.ts](mdc:src/components/index.ts) in alphabetical order
- Use the `@/components` import path for clean imports
- Components follow React.FC pattern with TypeScript interfaces

## Design System Principles

- **Apple-level precision**: Components are designed with refined interactions and micro-animations
- **Consistent spacing**: Use the spacing scale defined in Tailwind config
- **Semantic color system**: Use CSS variables for theming (background, foreground, muted, etc.)
- **Typography hierarchy**: Use the Typography component for all text with proper semantic variants